The paper proposes a deep learning model for inverse visual question answering, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, which focuses on computer vision. The paper also uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in NLP tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (computational linguistics) or cs.AI (artificial intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its model using multiple metrics, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (machine learning) or cs.IR (information retrieval).
